# SaaS Multi-Tenant Warehouse Inventory Management App Plan

## Tech Stack

Use:

- Next.js 16 with App Router
- TypeScript
- ESLint
- Prisma
- Neon Postgres
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Shadcn UI
- Zod
- React Hook Form
- @hookform/resolvers
- Better Auth

Use Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, and ESLint as the project foundation.

---

# Application Goal

Build a SaaS multi-tenant warehouse inventory management platform where companies can manage warehouses, inventory items, stock levels, receiving, picking, shipping, users, roles, and activity logs.

Each tenant/company must have isolated data.

---

# Core Features

## 1. Authentication

Use Better Auth for:

- Sign up
- Sign in
- Sign out
- Sessions
- Protected routes
- Organization/tenant-aware access
- Role-based authorization

Suggested roles:

```ts
OWNER
ADMIN
MANAGER
STAFF
VIEWER
```

## 2. Multi-Tenant Structure

Every major business record should belong to a `tenantId`.

Core tenant model:

- Tenant
- User
- Membership
- Warehouse
- InventoryItem
- StockLocation
- InventoryStock
- Supplier
- PurchaseOrder
- Receiving
- Shipment
- Order
- ActivityLog

Users can belong to one or more tenants through Membership.

## 3. Main App Sections

### Public Pages

- Landing page
- Pricing page
- Features page
- Sign in
- Sign up

### Protected Dashboard

- Overview dashboard
- Warehouses
- Inventory
- Stock levels
- Receiving
- Orders
- Shipments
- Suppliers
- Reports
- Team members
- Settings

